                  </hi>. I am a general salesman, and live in Whitechapel-road. On the 4th of July, about a quarter past two o'clock in the after<lb></lb>noon, I heard a noise at the door—I turned my head, an I saw the prisoner running away with the boots in his hand, close to the door—I pursued him—he threw them down—I followed, and took him without losing sight of him—these are my boots—(<hi rend="italic">looking at them</hi>)—they had been on a stall-board in front of the house.</p>
